featured_reviews.review_id:
I recently had the privilege of visiting a beautiful mosque (JAMA MASJID ABU BAKAR SIDDIQUE) in my community, and I must say it was an awe-inspiring experience that left a profound impact on me. As someone who appreciates the diverse cultures and religious traditions that enrich our world, I was deeply moved by the ambiance, architectural grandeur, and the overall spiritual atmosphere of this remarkable place of worship.

From the moment I stepped inside, I was immediately struck by the serene and tranquil environment. The mosque's architectural design was nothing short of breathtaking, with intricate patterns and elegant calligraphy adorning the walls and ceilings. The interplay of light and shadow created a mesmerizing effect, further enhancing the ambiance of the prayer hall.

The mosque was meticulously maintained, reflecting the devotion and care of the community that worships there. The cleanliness and orderliness of the premises were truly commendable, creating an inviting space for visitors and worshippers alike. It was evident that great effort had been put into maintaining the mosque as a sacred sanctuary for spiritual contemplation.

What impressed me the most was the warm and inclusive atmosphere fostered within the mosque. Despite being from a different religious background, I was welcomed with open arms by the friendly and hospitable staff and fellow worshippers. They were more than willing to answer any questions I had and engage in meaningful conversations about their faith and the mosque's role within the community.

featured_reviews.review_id:
During my visit, I had the privilege of witnessing the congregational prayers, which were conducted with reverence and discipline. It was heartening to see the sense of unity and devotion among the worshipers.

Qadri Masjid also offers a well-maintained facility, including a library where visitors can learn more about Islamic history and culture. The imam and members of the mosque were gracious and accommodating, eager to share their knowledge and engage in dialogue.

Overall, Qadri Masjid is not only a place of worship but a center of cultural and spiritual enrichment. It serves as a bridge between tradition and modernity, inviting people from all walks of life to explore its beauty and learn about the Islamic heritage. I would highly recommend a visit to experience the deep sense of spirituality and community that Qadri Masjid embodies.

featured_reviews.review_id: A spacious and well constructed mosque that has also become a favourite spot for many students  to offer Juma prayer. This mosque is no less than some Mughal monument. Beautiful in it's entirety , this is one place you can retire to for peace and tranquility. This Mosque is situated adjacent to New Library at West, backyard of Dr. Zakir Hussain mausoleum at North and Jamia School campus at east. Mosque is housed in a campus which has its own boundary perimeter with garden on all 4 sides. The main Mosque campus has entries from 3 sides except West. Mosque has an inner Sehan which houses approximately 8 rows consisting of 100 individuals in a row. The exterior part has an open air hall which can house 20+ rows of 80 rows each with covered alley on both sides of 10 individual capacity each row. Further, during Juma Salat there is arrangement of prayers in gardens on all 3 sides...This place Is Serene, peaceful, beautiful, Spacious you will feel the warmth and spiritual peace here...!!
